Spanish Stocks: CAM, Iberdrola, Gamesa, Zinkia Shares Move Today

-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 
2011-04-04T11:53:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-04/spanish-stocks-almirall-caja-de-ahorros-del-mediterraneo-move.html
Spain ’s IBEX 35 index rose 59.60, or
0.6 percent, to 10,789.5 at 1:35 p.m. in  Madrid . The Madrid
Stock Exchange General Index also advanced 0.6 percent.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Spanish market. Symbols are in parentheses after company names.  Caja de Ahorros del Mediterraneo (CAM)   dropped for a
fourth day, losing 8.8 percent to 5.61 euros. The Bank of Spain
has contacted several smaller Spanish lenders to find a buyer
for Caja de Ahorros del Mediterraneo, known as CAM, after
Spain’s largest banks showed little interest in the caja, El
Confidencial reported.  The Spanish savings bank will seek 2.8 billion euros ($4
billion) from a state rescue fund after the collapse of a
planned merger.  Gamesa Corporacion Tecnologica SA (GAM SM) climbed 1.8
percent to 7.50 euros, rising for a third day. Spain’s biggest
maker of  wind turbines  is among European stocks with M&A
potential, according to JPMorgan Chase & Co.  Iberdrola SA (IBE)   rose 0.8 percent to 6.26 euros as
Iberdrola Renovables SA won approval from Scottish regulators to
increase the capacity of its two biggest wind farms in the
nation, the company said in an e-mailed press release.  Zinkia Entertainment SA (ZNK)   advanced 1.3 percent to
1.61 euros after the production company reached an agreement to
buy shares representing 51 percent of London-based Cake
Entertainment Ltd.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Manuel Baigorri in Madrid at 
 mbaigorri@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Rummer at 
